---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Home"
  description="Firm Ground — a rigorous Christian apologetics resource for believers seeking a foundation and skeptics seeking honest engagement."
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-16 md:py-24">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="mb-20">
      <div class="mb-6 inline-block">
        <span class="font-sans text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gold-600 dark:text-gold-400 px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-gold-200 dark:border-gold-800 bg-gold-50 dark:bg-gold-900/20">
          Evidence-Based Apologetics
        </span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-ink-950 dark:text-parchment-50 leading-tight mb-6 text-balance">
        Christianity's claims<br class="hidden md:block" /> examined honestly
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-ink-600 dark:text-parchment-400 font-serif leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-8">
        For believers who want a stronger foundation. For skeptics who want straight answers.
        Primary sources, mainstream scholarship, and honest engagement with the hard questions.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a
          href="/bible-reliability"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-ink-900 dark:bg-parchment-100 text-white dark:text-ink-900 font-sans font-medium text-sm hover:bg-ink-700 dark:hover:bg-parchment-200 transition-colors"
        >
          Start with Bible Reliability
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth={2}>
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/methodology"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-parchment-300 dark:border-ink-700 text-ink-700 dark:text-parchment-300 font-sans font-medium text-sm hover:bg-parchment-100 dark:hover:bg-ink-900 transition-colors"
        >
          Our methodology
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Two audiences -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-20">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-parchment-200 dark:border-ink-800 bg-white dark:bg-ink-900 p-6">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-gold-100 dark:bg-gold-900/30 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gold-600 dark:text-gold-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth={2}>
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-ink-900 dark:text-parchment-100 mb-2">For Believers</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-600 dark:text-parchment-400 leading-relaxed font-sans">
          You believe — but when a skeptic asks a hard question, you don't have an answer.
          Here you'll find the evidence that makes faith a reasoned position, not just a tradition.
          With primary sources, not just talking points.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-parchment-200 dark:border-ink-800 bg-white dark:bg-ink-900 p-6">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900/30 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth={2}>
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M21 21l-4.35-4.35M17 11A6 6 0 105 11a6 6 0 0012 0z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-ink-900 dark:text-parchment-100 mb-2">For Skeptics</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-600 dark:text-parchment-400 leading-relaxed font-sans">
          Someone sent you here. We've tried to represent your position fairly, cite the scholars you respect,
          and engage the strongest version of the skeptical arguments — not the strawman.
          We think the evidence warrants more than dismissal.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Sections -->
    <div class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-ink-900 dark:text-parchment-100 mb-8">Start Exploring</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a
          href="/bible-reliability"
          class="group rounded-xl border border-parchment-200 dark:border-ink-800 bg-white dark:bg-ink-900 p-5 hover:border-gold-300 dark:hover:border-gold-700 hover:shadow-md transition-all"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-3">
            <span class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-ink-900 dark:text-parchment-100 group-hover:text-gold-700 dark:group-hover:text-gold-400 transition-colors">
              Bible Reliability
            </span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-ink-300 dark:text-ink-600 group-hover:text-gold-500 mt-1 transition-colors" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth={2}>
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink-500 dark:text-parchment-500 leading-relaxed font-sans">
            Manuscript evidence, textual criticism, Dead Sea Scrolls, canonization history, and
            common objections — with interactive data visualizations.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
            {['Manuscript Evidence', 'Textual Variants', 'Dead Sea Scrolls'].map((t) => (
              <span class="text-[10px] px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-parchment-100 dark:bg-ink-800 text-ink-500 dark:text-parchment-500 font-sans">
                {t}
              </span>
            ))}
          </div>
        </a>

        {['Historical Jesus', 'The Resurrection', 'Fulfilled Prophecy', 'Biblical Archaeology', 'Comparative Religion'].map((s) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-parchment-200/50 dark:border-ink-800/50 bg-parchment-50 dark:bg-ink-900/50 p-5 opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed">
            <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-2">
              <span class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-ink-700 dark:text-parchment-300">{s}</span>
              <span class="text-[10px] font-sans px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-parchment-200 dark:bg-ink-800 text-ink-400 dark:text-parchment-600">
                Coming soon
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What this site is not -->
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-parchment-200 dark:border-ink-800 bg-white dark:bg-ink-900 p-6 mb-20">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-ink-900 dark:text-parchment-100 mb-4">What this site is not</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-3 text-sm font-sans text-ink-600 dark:text-parchment-400">
        {[
          'It is not proof that Christianity is true',
          'It does not resolve every biblical tension',
          'It is not a place for mockery or dismissal',
          'It does not pretend every question is settled',
          'It is not "KJV-only" or fringe apologetics',
          'It does not use inflation or cherry-picked data',
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-gold-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">—</span>
            <span>{item}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-sans text-ink-500 dark:text-parchment-500 leading-relaxed">
        We are trying to build confidence in the evidence where the evidence warrants it — and to say honestly where it doesn't.
        The goal is serious engagement, not cheerleading.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
